                                  ItemStats
=====================================================================
Making items is a very delicate process.  That is why there is this
help.  Use the chart below for the AC values for the items in your 
area.  Remember that jewelry does not have any AC values.

Points for armor
============================
Here you use points to determine how to distribute added affects to eq.
The formula is (eq level) * 2 = Points.  For instance a level 80 piece of eq
gets 160 points.  Of course the formula for jewlery is a different since
jewelry has no AC, so the formula would be (eq level) * 2.5 = Points.

Here is the point values:
============================
1 point      = 1 mana
1 point      = 1 hp
1 point      = 5 move
5 points     = 1 save, savingbreath, savingpara, savingrod, etc.
5 points     = 1 ac
10 points    = 1 hitroll
10 points    = 1 damroll
15 points    = 1 stat (1 str,dex,con,wis, or int)

Keep in mind that the sum of the points should NOT exceed the points
of the piece of eq.  Also you may put in a negative added affect for
eq.  Ie. adding a -2 con to a level 50 piece of eq would give it 65
points.  Because each stat is 15 and you only get half of the value 
for negative added affects.  Except for AC DO NOT imply this for AC
since -AC is a good thing.

About poweritems, they are only to be used with permission of a 108+
and after reading the help thourghly.  Also you must put 1 in the name
Ie. curved scimitar1.  DO NOT forget this, it is important.  You may
be requested to note your poweritems to an IMM 108+ and they may add
them for you.
